Orum
Orum is one of the most talked-about AI-powered dialers in 2026. Its core differentiator is speed — it uses AI to detect voicemails, busy signals, and disconnected numbers in real time, connecting reps only to live answers. This dramatically increases the number of live conversations a rep can have per hour.

Sales teams using Orum report getting 5 to 8 times more live conversations per day compared to manual dialing. The platform also includes live call collaboration features, allowing managers to join calls silently, coach reps in real time, and review calls through its built-in analytics.

Best for: High-volume outbound teams that need to maximize live connect rates at scale.

ConnectAndSell
ConnectAndSell takes a different approach. Rather than giving reps a smarter dialer, it offloads the actual dialing, navigating, and waiting to a service layer — delivering reps only to live prospects. The result is that a rep can have conversations with 8 to 10 qualified prospects per hour rather than spending most of their day in voicemail land.

It integrates with major CRMs and can pull directly from existing lead lists. For companies with mature outbound programs looking to dramatically increase rep productivity without hiring more people, ConnectAndSell offers a compelling ROI.

Best for: Mature outbound sales teams looking to maximize rep productivity without expanding headcount.

Chorus by ZoomInfo
Chorus, now deeply integrated with ZoomInfo's data platform, offers powerful call recording and conversation intelligence with the added advantage of ZoomInfo's unmatched B2B contact and company data.

For teams already using ZoomInfo for prospecting, Chorus creates a seamless feedback loop — call outcomes inform prospecting strategy, and prospecting data enriches call preparation. Its AI surfaces deal risk, tracks competitor mentions, and highlights coaching moments across every recorded interaction.

Best for: ZoomInfo users who want tightly integrated conversation intelligence and prospect data.

Dialpad Ai Sales
Dialpad Ai Sales is one of the most AI-forward calling platforms in 2026. Its real-time transcription, sentiment analysis, and live coaching are built natively into the platform rather than bolted on through third-party integrations.

The platform automatically surfaces objection responses, competitor mentions, and action items during the call, without the rep needing to take manual notes. After the call, it generates a clean summary and syncs outcomes to the CRM automatically.

Dialpad is also cloud-native and device-agnostic, making it a strong fit for distributed or remote sales teams that need a reliable, feature-rich platform accessible from anywhere.

Best for: Remote and hybrid sales teams that prioritize native AI features and ease of use.

Cognism
Cognism is best understood as a premium intelligence layer that fuels cold calling rather than a dialer itself. It provides verified mobile phone numbers for B2B prospects across North America and Europe, combined with intent data, technographic filters, and compliance-checked contact data including GDPR and CCPA alignment.

For B2B sales teams in the US, Cognism's Diamond Data — where phone numbers are verified through human research — delivers significantly higher connect rates because reps are reaching numbers that actually ring. Integrating Cognism with a dialer like Orum or Aircall creates a powerful combination of clean data and fast execution.

Best for: B2B teams that want the highest-quality phone data to fuel their outbound programs.

How to Choose the Right Cold Calling Tool for Your Team
The right tool depends on the size of your team, the complexity of your sales cycle, and the channels you use. Here are a few practical questions to guide your decision:

What is your primary pain point — not enough conversations, not enough qualified conversations, or inconsistent messaging?

If the problem is volume, look at power dialers and AI dialers like Orum or ConnectAndSell. If the problem is quality and coaching, prioritize conversation intelligence platforms like Gong or Outreach's Kaia. If the problem is data — bad phone numbers, reaching the wrong people — start with a data platform like Cognism or Apollo.

Do you need a point solution or an all-in-one platform? Companies scaling their outbound motion often start with a single tool and layer in additional capabilities over time. Others prefer a unified platform that consolidates prospecting, dialing, sequencing, and analytics in one place.

What is your budget? Enterprise platforms like Salesloft, Outreach, and Gong come with enterprise pricing. Mid-market options like Apollo and Aircall offer strong value for teams that do not need the full enterprise feature set.

Integrating Cold Calling Into a Full-Funnel B2B Strategy
Cold calling works best when it is one part of a coordinated, full-funnel strategy rather than an isolated tactic. The most effective B2B sales programs in 2026 connect calling with content syndication, email marketing, account-based marketing, and appointment setting into a unified pipeline engine.

When a prospect downloads a piece of content or engages with a targeted ad, that signal can trigger a timely, relevant phone call from a sales rep — one that feels like a natural continuation of the buyer's journey rather than a random interruption. That is the power of intent-driven selling.

